To download flask you first need to make sure python3 is installed
$ pip install virtualenv
-it should spit out the path to where the virtualenv script was installed
cd to that directory
and run it pointing it to your project (choose a name)
$ cd /home/cvte/.local/bin
$ ls
$ ./virtualenv TraFix-project

then activate the enviroment
$ source TraFix-project/bin/activate
this should change your prompt to your project name
install flask to develop the app
(TraFix-project) $ pip install flask

verify it worked
(TraFix-project) $ python -c "print('hello')"

